headline: Tariffs will likely raise toy prices, toymaker warns
summary: Tariffs on toys have dropped from 145% to about 30%, but higher costs will still likely reach consumers by 2026. Jay Foreman, Basic Fun! CEO, joins Market Catalysts to explain how manufacturers and retailers are managing the impact and what to expect this holiday season. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Catalysts here.

headline: Hasbro (HAS) Upgraded to Strong Buy: What Does It Mean for the Stock?
summary: Hasbro (HAS) has been upgraded to a Zacks Rank #1 (Strong Buy), reflecting growing optimism about the company's earnings prospects. This might drive the stock higher in the near term.
